! Multi-Cursor

Edit multiple locations simultaneously with multiple cursors.

!! Features

* ''Add cursors'': Ctrl+Click to add cursor at click position
* ''Select occurrences'': Select next or all occurrences of selection
* ''Column cursors'': Add cursors above/below current position
* ''Synchronized editing'': Type, delete, paste at all cursors simultaneously

!! Keyboard Shortcuts

|!Key |!Action |
|Ctrl+Click |Add cursor at click position |
|Ctrl+D |Select next occurrence of word/selection |
|Ctrl+Shift+L |Select all occurrences |
|Alt+Shift+Up |Add cursor on line above |
|Alt+Shift+Down |Add cursor on line below |
|Escape |Clear all secondary cursors |
|Arrow keys |Move all cursors |
|Ctrl+Arrow |Word-wise movement for all cursors |

!! Configuration

|!Tiddler |!Values |!Default |
|`$:/config/Editor/EnableMultiCursor` |`yes` / `no` |`yes` |

!! Widget Attribute

```
<$edit-text enableMultiCursor="yes"/>
```

!! Notes

* Regular click clears secondary cursors
* Shift+Click extends selection (standard behavior)
* Overlapping cursors are automatically merged
* Works with most editing operations